# 2. 変化とともに

Akito: Alright, I think we're all warmed up now.
Toya: Yes, I feel ready.
Akito: Then, let's get started. Today... We'll keep practicing what we were doing the other day.
An: Oh, I really liked that! It's really fun and a good source of motivation.
Kohane: Yeah! Then, as for teams—
???: <Hey! Have you guys started practicing already?!>
Akito: Hm?
Toya: Rin and Len. With Miku and Luka in tow...
Len: <Morning, you guys! We're here to watch you practice!>
Kohane: Watch us practice?
Luka: <You've been practicing in a variety of different ways lately, which has been really fun to watch. So, we decided to come over again!>
Akito: Fun...? Well, I guess it is good to have people watching.
An: Haha. I'm glad you guys came! It's hard not to feel more motivated with an audience watching!
Len: <Hehe! Thanks! So, what are you guys gonna do today?>
Akito: More two-on-two battles like we did the other day, but with different teams.
Rin: <Yes! I love how a song feels so different depending on who sings it with who!>
Akito: Anyway, if we continue based on last time... Kohane, you and I are gonna be on the same team today.
Kohane: Okay! Let's do our best, Shinonome.
Toya: Feel free to let us know if anything catches your attention, Miku, everyone.
Miku: <Okay, we will.>
Akito: Then, let's begin. You guys can start us off.
An: Alright... Toya, let's kick their butts!
An & Toya: ♪————————!!
Len: <Whoa...!>
Luka: <Those two are off to a great start! They're harmonizing so well♪>
Miku: <Yes, they're achieving a nice balance. An brings energy, while Toya provides stability... They're drawing out the best in each other.>
An & Toya: ♪————————!! ♪————————!!
Akito: (They sound good... And they're in perfect sync.)
Kohane: Let's go, Shinonome.
Akito: Okay.
Akito & Kohane: ♪————————!
Akito: Phew... Okay, let's take a break here.
An: Yeah, sounds good! We've all had a chance to sing!
Kohane: Hehe. I really do like this way of practicing since it's both fun and rewarding.
Toya: I agree. Not only do you have to adjust your performance to your teammate, but it also allows you to bring out the best in one another.
An: And battling like this creates the kind of tension you'd feel in a real event.
Akito: Yeah.
Akito: Ken helped us practice leading up to RAD BLAST, but that isn't gonna be possible now.
Akito: We have to keep coming up with the best ways for us to practice and improve.
Kohane: Right!
Luka: <Hehe. I sort of feel like singing now after watching all of you practice.>
Len: <More to the point, the next time you guys are in SEKAI, you should battle against us!>
An: Oh, that sounds fun. But we're not gonna go easy on you.
Rin: <Oh? That also applies to you guys!>
Akito: ...? Sorry, that's mine.
Akito: They're making some final confirmation about tomorrow's event. I'll send this over to you guys a little later.
Miku: <Oh, that's right. You have that event tomorrow.>
Luka: <Wait, really?! It's been quite a while since you all last entered into an event.>
Kohane: Yes, it has. And we haven't done any since RAD BLAST...
An: We've mostly been spending our time on English lessons, uploading videos with translated lyrics and practicing on our own.
An: Now that you mention it, we haven't performed in front of an audience in so long! I can't wait!
Toya: Yes, me neither... But we'll also need to stay focused.
Akito: Especially since we've been asked to perform as special guests.
Len: <Wait, guests?! Does that mean you guys were invited?>
Miku: <Yes. Not only that, they're apparently performing at one of the live houses where they trained. One that attracts a lot of high-level talent.>
Rin: <Really?! And you guys have been invited as special guests?! That's awesome!>
Akito: We were also surprised when they reached out to us, but they apparently decided to invite us after hearing about RAD BLAST.
Toya: Which is all the more reason why we'll need to put on a solid performance.
Kohane: Right! Let's do our best to make sure we don't disappoint!
Len: <Go knock their socks off, you guys! We'll all be rooting for you.>
An: Oh, we will! They won't know what hit them!
Rin: <Huh...? What's wrong, Akito? Is something bothering you?>
Akito: Oh...
Akito: Nothing. I was just thinking about how to reply to this message.
Akito: Anyway, the crowd and other performers are apparently really looking forward to seeing us.
Akito: So, let's make sure our set list and performance live up to the hype.
Kohane: Yeah, okay!
Toya: ...
